  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Coco's mother asked her that night why she looked so quiet at dinner, and Coco just smiled and said it was a good kind of quiet.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，Coco 的媽媽問她晚餐時為什麼這麼安靜，Coco 只是笑了笑，說這是一種很好的安靜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Nobody said anything for a while after Mr. Pan finished speaking.",
      "zh": "潘老師說完之後，有好一會兒沒有人說話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice was the first to break the silence. \"Can we make an episode about this?\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 先打破沉默：「我們可以做一集關於這件事的節目嗎？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Only if you want us to,\" Coco added quickly. \"You don't have to say yes.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 很快補充：「只有在你願意的時候才做，你不用答應。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan thought about it for a long moment before answering.",
      "zh": "潘老師想了好一會兒才回答。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Not the whole story,\" he said. \"Not my name as the boy in it. Just... the idea.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「不要講整件事，也不要說那個男孩是我，就講⋯⋯這個想法就好。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's exactly what Mei said, too,\" Bernice said. \"About the practice room.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「Mei 之前也是這麼說的，關於練習室的事。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan almost laughed. \"Then maybe you two have learned the most important rule of all.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師幾乎笑了出來：「那也許你們兩個已經學會了最重要的那條規則。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Which one?\" Coco asked.",
      "zh": "Coco 問：「哪一條？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Ask what someone actually wants,\" he said, \"before you decide what their story means.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「先問一個人真正想要什麼，再決定他們的故事代表什麼意義。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That weekend, Coco tried writing the words for the new episode three separate times.",
      "zh": "那個週末，Coco 試著把新一集的內容寫了三次。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The first try explained every case in detail. She did not keep it.",
      "zh": "第一次嘗試詳細解釋了每一個案子，她沒有留下這個版本。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The second try tried to be funny, like the bakery episode. It didn't feel right either.",
      "zh": "第二次嘗試想寫得像麵包店那一集一樣好笑，但感覺也不太對。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The third try was short. It simply said: some people build something for others because nobody built it for them.",
      "zh": "第三次嘗試很短，只寫了一句話：有些人為別人建立一件事，是因為當初沒有人為他們做過。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice read it once and put down her phone. \"That's the one,\" she said.",
      "zh": "Bernice 讀了一次，把手機放下：「就是這個，」她說。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They recorded the episode together, all three of them in the room this time: Coco, Bernice, and Mr. Pan.",
      "zh": "這一次三個人一起錄音：Coco、Bernice，還有潘老師。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan spoke only one line on the recording, near the end.",
      "zh": "潘老師在錄音裡只說了一句話，在快結束的時候。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"If something helped you once,\" he said, \"the best thing you can do is help make sure it's still there for someone else.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「如果有件事曾經幫過你，最好的做法就是確保它還在，好讓它能幫到別人。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "When the episode ended, none of them spoke for a moment. It felt like the right kind of quiet.",
      "zh": "節目結束後，他們三個有那麼一刻都沒有說話，那是一種恰到好處的安靜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On Saturdays, Coco had to cook breakfast, feed the neighbor's cat, and cut the grass in the small yard behind her building.",
      "zh": "每個星期六，Coco 得煮早餐、餵鄰居的貓，還要修剪公寓後面小院子的草。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She would draw a quick chore list, cross off each task, and save the hardest one for last.",
      "zh": "她會畫一張簡單的家事清單，做完一項就劃掉，把最難的留到最後。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Her aunt always said it was better to prepare a plan first than to enjoy a free afternoon with no plan at all.",
      "zh": "阿姨總是說，與其毫無計畫地享受一個空閒下午，不如先準備好計畫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Once she finished, Coco liked to celebrate with a short bike ride, just to clear her mind before homework.",
      "zh": "做完之後，Coco 喜歡騎一小段腳踏車慶祝一下，寫作業前先清空腦袋。"
    }
  ],
